About M365 Substrate Intelligence: 
Our team has a diverse set of PMs with expertise in artificial intelligence, big data, and intelligent end-user experience. We delight in digging deeper to understand our customers and develop delightful user experiences that anticipate people's needs, help them prioritize, and get started faster. We build coherent and consistent assistance throughout the M365 product suite, such as Focused Inbox, Suggested Replies, Text Predictions, and other features that millions of users rely on daily. 
Responsibilities 
This PM will be responsible for engaging and influencing the Microsoft-wide efforts around Responsible AI (RAI), while defining and directing the implementation plan for the core M365 team. This will include system-building across the organization: data set development, assessment tools, model lifecycle management, and any necessary platform evolutions. Working as a team we will make it scalable for every feature developer to honor both the spirit and the letter of our RAI standards: accountability, transparency, fairness, reliability & safety, privacy & security, and inclusiveness. 
Qualifications 
Required Qualifications: 
5+ years of applied AI experience (or equivalent) 
MS degree (PhD preferred) in Computer Science, Engineering, or related technical field 
Preferred Qualificatons: 
Strong experience with and a passion for artificial intelligence 
Passion for and experience adapting AI models for increased fairness and inclusivity 
Interest in and knowledge of key ethical challenges related to AI and data usage 
Ability to handle ambiguity and rapid change while continuously delivering an evolving product 
Desire to effectively negotiate and collaborate across teams and organizations 
Strong verbal/written communication skills for both technical and non-technical audiences 
Demonstrated strong performance in prior roles 
Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form. 
